18. Use RichText Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The RichText widget in Flutter is used to display text with multiple styles in a single line or paragraph.

Allows combining different styles (color, size, font)
Uses TextSpan to define styled parts
Useful for highlighting specific word

// main code 

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: RichTextExample(),
    );
  }
}

class RichTextExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("RichText Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: RichText(
          text: TextSpan(
            text: "Hello ",
            style: TextStyle(color: Colors.black, fontSize: 20),
            children: [
              TextSpan(
                text: "Flutter",
                style: TextStyle(
                  color: Colors.blue,
                  fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,
                ),
              ),
              TextSpan(
                text: " World!",
                style: TextStyle(color: Colors.green),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}